The paper discusses linear programming techniques for deducing corollaries of non-classic inequalities for Shannon's entropy, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also extensively uses symmetry considerations, which is a topic related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The applications of the copy lemma discussed in the paper are relevant to coding theory and cryptography, which fall under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC) and computer security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses an example of improving the lower bound for a secret sharing scheme, which is a topic related to social and information networks (cs.SI).
